title: The Best of Booker T. & The MG's - FLAC (Big Papi) 1986
description:
Source: 1986 CD
 
[img]https://yuq.me/users/15/891/rhja05JuNK.png[/img]
By The Hit Man
 
[quote]Steve Cropper and Donald "Duck" Dunn never publicly received, during the explosion of the Soul / R&B era ,credit for developing and playing some of the best Soul / R&B music...period!They were acknowledged as studio / back up musicians at best.There are not any bad cuts on this CD. True, fans of only Booker T & MG's will nit pick and have issues. These songs and the albums they came from represent yet another avenue of Soul / R&B that had not previously existed. Enjoy it for what it was and is....creativity at its best that helped define an era. And is still worth listening to today![/quote]
